{"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"metadata":{"title":"Getting Started","roleHeading":"Article","role":"article"},"kind":"article","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/dev.alexanderweiss.swiftui_theming\/documentation\/SwiftUITheming\/GettingStarted","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Adding-swiftui-theming-as-a-dependency","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Adding swiftui-theming as a dependency"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let package = Package(","  dependencies: [","    .package(","      url: \"https:\/\/github.com\/alexanderwe\/swiftui-theming\",","      from: \"0.1.1\"","    ),","  ],","  targets: [","    .target(","      name: \"<target-name>\",","      dependencies: [","        .product(","          name: \"Theming\",","          package: \"swiftui-theming\"","        )","      ]","    )","  ]",")"]},{"anchor":"Create-your-first-theme","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Create your first theme"},{"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Be sure to checkout "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/dev.alexanderweiss.swiftui_theming\/tutorials\/MeetSwiftUITheming"},{"type":"text","text":" for an interactive tutorial."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"anchor":"Step-1-Define-Color-Styles","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Step 1: Define Color Styles"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Before creating a new theme, define the color styles available in your app:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["import Theming","","extension ThemeColorStyle {","    \/\/\/ A style for primary labels","    static let primaryLabel: Self = Self(name: \"primaryLabel\")","    \/\/ Define additional styles as needed","}"]},{"anchor":"Step-2-Create-a-Theme","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Step 2: Create a Theme"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"With color styles defined, implement a method to create a theme. Each theme requires to at least have a name and a color mapping. Depending on your needs you may need different mappings on different platforms since not all color ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/dev.alexanderweiss.swiftui_theming\/documentation\/Theming\/ThemeColor","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" variants are available on all platforms.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["import Theming","\/\/ MARK: - Available Themes","extension Theme {","    static let `default`: Theme = .createDefaultTheme()","}","","\/\/ MARK: - Theme Creation","extension Theme {","    private static func createDefaultTheme() -> Theme {","        let colors: Theme.ColorMap = [","            .primaryLabel: ThemeColor(lightColor: .primary, darkColor: .primary)","        ]","        return Theme(name: \"Default\", colors: colors)","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Make-App-themeable","text":"Make App themeable"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To enable theming in your app, inject a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/dev.alexanderweiss.swiftui_theming\/documentation\/Theming\/ThemeManager"},{"text":" instance into your app’s scenes.","type":"text"}]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Step-1-Initialize-ThemeManager","text":"Step 1: Initialize `ThemeManager`"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Declare a ","type":"text"},{"code":"@State","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" property to hold the ","type":"text"},{"code":"ThemeManager","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in your app definition:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["import SwiftUI","import Theming","","@main","struct MyApp: App {","    @State var myThemeManager: ThemeManager = ThemeManager(initialTheme: .default)","","    var body: some Scene {","        WindowGroup {","            ContentView()","        }","        .withThemeManager(themeManager: myThemeManager)","    }","}"]},{"text":"Step 2: Access Theme Colors in Views","anchor":"Step-2-Access-Theme-Colors-in-Views","type":"heading","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use the ","type":"text"},{"code":".themeColor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" method to apply theme colors in your SwiftUI views:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct ContentView: View {","    var body: some View {","        Text(\"Hello World\")","            .foregroundStyle(.themeColor(for: .primaryLabel))","    }","}"]},{"text":"SwiftUI previews","anchor":"SwiftUI-previews","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In order to test your themes in SwiftUI previews, you can either inject a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/dev.alexanderweiss.swiftui_theming\/documentation\/Theming\/ThemeManager","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" or a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/dev.alexanderweiss.swiftui_theming\/documentation\/Theming\/Theme","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["#Preview(","    traits: .withThemeManager(ThemeManager(initialTheme: .createDefaultTheme()))",") {","    Text(\"Hello, world!\")","            .foregroundStyle(.themeColor(for: .primaryLabel))","}"]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["#Preview(","    traits: .withTheme(.createDefaultTheme())",") {","    Text(\"Hello, world!\")","            .foregroundStyle(.themeColor(for: .primaryLabel))","}"]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/dev.alexanderweiss.swiftui_theming\/documentation\/Overview"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftuitheming\/gettingstarted"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to integrate SwiftUI Theming into your project."}],"references":{"doc://dev.alexanderweiss.swiftui_theming/documentation/Overview":{"type":"topic","title":"SwiftUI Theming Documentation","kind":